{"type":"message","id":"8bb21f99","parentId":"4308da01","timestamp":"2026-02-11T16:02:17.242Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-02-11 18:02 GMT+2] Роль: SECURITY. Проведи аудит файла src/api/dmarket.py. Проверь: 1. Утечки API-ключей в логах. 2. Безопасность хранения и передачи подписей. Отвечай СТРОГО по формату JSON из docs/SUB_AGENT_GUIDE.md. Никакого лишнего текста."}],"timestamp":1770825737240}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd922608","parentId":"8bb21f99","timestamp":"2026-02-11T16:02:18.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1770825738312_10","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/api/dmarket.py"},"thoughtSignature":"EjQKMgG+Pvb7wV5aCXNJlthHSOerh5pcSrZdN9n1DvaVr1gDHuV8m4HtrWg+eILUYHQUNaQx"},{"type":"text","text":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":8357,"output":23,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8380,"cost":{"input":0.0041785,"output":0.000069,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0042474999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770825737242}}
{"type":"message","id":"8da2cff1","parentId":"fd922608","timestamp":"2026-02-11T16:02:18.344Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1770825738312_10","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nDMarket API Client (Clean Architecture Implementation).\nFollows Google Cloud Application Development guidelines for robustness and structure.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport asyncio\nimport hashlib\nimport hmac\nimport json\nimport logging\nimport time\nimport os\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\nfrom urllib.parse import urlencode\nimport httpx\n\n# Dependencies\ntry:\n    import nacl.signing\n    from nacl.encoding import HexEncoder\n    HAS_NACL = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    HAS_NACL = False\n\n# Core Config (One-way dependency)\nfrom src.core.config import CONFIG\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"api.dmarket\")\n\nclass DMarketAPI:\n    \"\"\"\n    Robust DMarket API Client.\n    Handles authentication, rate limiting, and multi-game switching.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    BASE_URL = \"https://api.dmarket.com\"\n\n    def __init__(self, public_key: str, secret_key: str, rate_limit: float = 0.2):\n        \"\"\"\n        Initialize the client.\n        \n        Args:\n            public_key: API Public Key\n            secret_key: API Secret Key\n            rate_limit: Minimum seconds between requests (basic throttling)\n        \"\"\"\n        self.public_key = public_key\n        self.secret_key = secret_key\n        self.rate_limit = rate_limit\n        self.last_request_time = 0.0\n        \n        # Initialize HTTP client with timeouts\n        self.client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n            timeout=30.0,\n            headers={\n                \"User-Agent\": \"OpenClaw-TradingBot/2.0\",\n                \"Accept\": \"application/json\"\n            }\n        )\n\n    def _generate_signature(self, method: str, path: str, body: str = \"\") -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Generates DMarket API Signature (Ed25519 or HMAC-SHA256).\n        \"\"\"\n        timestamp = str(int(time.time()))\n        string_to_sign = f\"{method}{path}{body}{timestamp}\"\n        \n        headers = {\n            \"X-Api-Key\": self.public_key,\n            \"X-Sign-Date\": timestamp,\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n        }\n\n        # Try Ed25519 first (Preferred by DMarket)\n        if HAS_NACL and len(self.secret_key) == 128: # Hex representation of 64 bytes\n            try:\n                signing_key = nacl.signing.SigningKey(bytes.fromhex(self.secret_key))\n                signed = signing_key.sign(string_to_sign.encode('utf-8'))\n                signature = signed.signature.hex()\n                headers[\"X-Request-Sign\"] = f\"dmar ed25519 {signature}\"\n                return headers\n            except Exception as e:\n                logger.warning(f\"Ed25519 signing failed, falling back to HMAC: {e}\")\n\n        # Fallback to HMAC-SHA256\n        signature = hmac.new(\n            self.secret_key.encode('utf-8'),\n            string_to_sign.encode('utf-8'),\n            hashlib.sha256\n        ).hexdigest()\n        headers[\"X-Request-Sign\"] = signature\n        return headers\n\n    async def __aenter__(self):\n        return self\n\n    async def __aexit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):\n        await self.close()\n\n    async def _request(\n        self, \n        method: str, \n        endpoint: str, \n        params: Optional[Dict] = None, \n        data: Optional[Dict] = None,\n        retries: int = 3\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Execute request with Retry logic (Exponential Backoff).\n        \"\"\"\n        # Rate Limiting\n        elapsed = time.time() - self.last_request_time\n        if elapsed < self.rate_limit:\n            await asyncio.sleep(self.rate_limit - elapsed)\n        \n        url = f\"{self.BASE_URL}{endpoint}\"\n        body_str = json.dumps(data) if data else \"\"\n        \n        # Build path for signature (must include query params strictly sorted)\n        path_for_sign = endpoint\n        if params:\n            sorted_params = sorted(params.items())\n            query_string = urlencode(sorted_params)\n            path_for_sign = f\"{endpoint}?{query_string}\"\n            # Ensure httpx uses the same order\n            # Note: We pass params to httpx, which usually sorts them, but to be 100% safe\n            # we should sign what we send. Using path_for_sign in signature.\n            # And letting httpx handle params (it usually matches).\n            # DMarket signature requires exact match.\n\n        for attempt in range(retries):\n            try:\n                headers = self._generate_signature(method, path_for_sign, body_str)\n                \n                response = await self.client.request(\n                    method, \n                    url, \n                    params=params, \n                    content=body_str, \n                    headers=headers\n                )\n                \n                self.last_request_time = time.time()\n\n                if response.status_code == 200:\n                    return response.json()\n                elif response.status_code == 429:\n                    logger.warning(f\"Rate limit hit. Sleeping... (Attempt {attempt+1}/{retries})\")\n                    await asyncio.sleep(2 ** attempt) # Exponential backoff\n                else:\n                    logger.error(f\"API Error {response.status_code}: {response.text}\")\n                    # Don't retry on client errors (400-403) unless it's strictly network\n                    if 400 <= response.status_code < 500 and response.status_code != 429:\n                        return {\"objects\": []} # Return empty to avoid crash\n            \n            except httpx.RequestError as e:\n                logger.error(f\"Network error: {e}\")\n                await asyncio.sleep(1)\n        \n        return {\"objects\": []} # Fallback\n\n    async def get_market_items(\n        self,\n        game: str,\n        limit: int = 50,\n        price_from: float = 0.0,\n        price_to: float = 0.0,\n        currency: str = \"USD\",\n        sort: str = \"price\"\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Fetch items for a specific game using GAME_CONFIG.\n        Endpoint: /exchange/v1/market/items (Standard Exchange API)\n        \"\"\"\n        game_config = CONFIG.GAMES.get(game)\n        if not game_config:\n            logger.error(f\"Game '{game}' not found in CONFIG.\")\n            return {\"objects\": []}\n\n        params = {\n            \"gameId\": game_config.dmarket_id,\n            \"limit\": limit,\n            \"currency\": currency,\n            \"orderBy\": sort,\n            \"priceFrom\": int(price_from * 100), # Convert to cents\n            \"priceTo\": int(price_to * 100)\n        }\n        \n        return await self._request(\"GET\", \"/exchange/v1/market/items\", params=params)\n\n    async def get_balance(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"\n        Get current USD balance.\n        Endpoint: /account/v1/balance\n        Returns: Balance in USD (float)\n        \"\"\"\n        data = await self._request(\"GET\", \"/account/v1/balance\")\n        # Response format: {\"usd\": 4550, \"dmc\": ...} (in cents)\n        cents = int(data.get(\"usd\", 0))\n        return float(cents) / 100.0\n\n    async def get_offers_by_title(self, title: str, game: str = \"csgo\", limit: int = 10) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Get specific offers for a title.\n        Endpoint: /exchange/v1/offers-by-title (Strictly from JSON)\n        \"\"\"\n        game_config = CONFIG.GAMES.get(game)\n        if not game_config: return {}\n\n        params = {\n            \"Title\": title,\n            \"GameID\": game_config.dmarket_id,\n            \"Limit\": limit,\n            \"Currency\": \"USD\"\n        }\n        return await self._request(\"GET\", \"/exchange/v1/offers-by-title\", params=params)\n\n    async def buy_item(self, item_id: str, price: int, game: str = \"csgo\") -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Execute Buy Order.\n        Endpoint: /exchange/v1/offers/buy\n        Payload: Price in coins (cents).\n        \"\"\"\n        payload = {\n            \"offers\": [\n                {\n                    \"offerId\": item_id,\n                    \"price\": {\"amount\": str(price), \"currency\": \"USD\"},\n                    \"type\": \"dmarket\"\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n        # Dry Run for now\n        logger.info(f\"DRY RUN BUY: {item_id} for {price} cents\")\n        return {\"status\": \"dry_run_success\"}\n\n    async def close(self):\n        await self.client.aclose()\n\n# --- Consilium Test Runner ---\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    from dotenv import load_dotenv\n    load_dotenv()\n    \n    # Configure Logging\n    logging.basicConfig(\n        level=logging.INFO,\n        format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s'\n    )\n\n    async def test_multigame():\n        pub = os.getenv(\"DMARKET_PUBLIC_KEY\")\n        sec = os.getenv(\"DMARKET_SECRET_KEY\")\n        \n        if not pub or not sec:\n            print(\"❌ Keys missing.\")\n            return\n\n        api = DMarketAPI(pub, sec)\n        print(\"🤖 DMarketAPI Initialized. Starting Multigame Test...\\n\")\n\n        games = [\"csgo\", \"dota2\", \"rust\", \"tf2\"]\n        \n        for game in games:\n            print(f\"📡 Requesting {game.upper()}...\")\n            data = await api.get_market_items(game, limit=5, price_from=1.0, price_to=10.0)\n            items = data.get(\"objects\", [])\n            \n            if items:\n                first = items[0]\n                price = float(first['price']['USD']) / 100\n                print(f\"✅ {game.upper()}: Success! Found {len(items)} items.\")\n                print(f\"   Sample: {first['title']} (${price})\")\n            else:\n                print(f\"⚠️ {game.upper()}: No items returned (or error).\")\n            \n            print(\"-\" * 30)\n        \n        await api.close()\n\n    asyncio.run(test_multigame())\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1770825738343}}
{"type":"message","id":"c750af74","parentId":"8da2cff1","timestamp":"2026-02-11T16:02:23.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"```json\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Аудит безопасности src/api/dmarket.py завершен. Критических уязвимостей (прямых утечек ключей) не обнаружено, однако выявлены риски логирования ошибок API и недостатки в механизме формирования подписей.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"category\": \"Logging & Information Exposure\",\n      \"severity\": \"MEDIUM\",\n      \"description\": \"В методе `_request` при получении ошибки API логируется `response.text`. Если API DMarket вернет в теле ошибки детали запроса (например, заголовки с API-ключом или подписью), это приведет к утечке чувствительных данных в логи.\",\n      \"location\": \"src/api/dmarket.py, строка 131\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Логировать только статус-код или фильтровать `response.text` перед записью в лог.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"Authentication & Signatures\",\n      \"severity\": \"LOW\",\n      \"description\": \"Метод `_generate_signature` использует `time.time()` для `X-Sign-Date`. При рассинхронизации времени сервера с API DMarket запросы будут отклоняться. Также отсутствует проверка на корректность формата `secret_key` перед использованием в HMAC.\",\n      \"location\": \"src/api/dmarket.py, строки 61-89\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Рекомендуется использовать NTP-синхронизацию. Добавить валидацию secret_key в `__init__`.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"Data Integrity\",\n      \"severity\": \"LOW\",\n      \"description\": \"В методе `_request` параметры запроса сортируются вручную для подписи, но передаются в `httpx.request(params=params)`. Хотя httpx обычно сохраняет порядок или сортирует их, для 100% надежности подписи рекомендуется передавать уже готовую строку запроса (query string) в URL.\",\n      \"location\": \"src/api/dmarket.py, строки 111-125\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Использовать готовую `query_string` при формировании финального URL запроса.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"safe_aspects\": [\n    \"API-ключи передаются через переменные окружения и не захардкожены в файле.\",\n    \"Реализована поддержка Ed25519 (библиотека PyNaCl), что является стандартом безопасности для DMarket.\",\n    \"Секретный ключ используется только для генерации подписи внутри метода и не передается в открытом виде.\"\n  ],\n  \"status\": \"SECURE_WITH_RESERVATIONS\"\n}\n```","textSignature":"EjQKMgG+Pvb7+ce5v5g+a5+A53xgeUgR72c3ZpJkkGJWQS8oyZn1JliuQKk98uPnbZh1Gqoe"}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":11008,"output":622,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11630,"cost":{"input":0.005503999999999999,"output":0.001866,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00737}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770825738345}}
